  "text": "where , , and are the absorbance of treated, untreated, and blank samples, respectively, which were studied as means of triplicate. IC 50 (concentration of drug decreasing 50% of cell viability) was prescribed by linear regression analysis [CITATION_1] . Reference drug, Glucantime® (Meglumine antimoniate), was kept at 4 ∘ C and diluted with RPMI 1640 medium at the time of incubation. Sterile distilled water was used to prepare stock solutions of all extracts of H. leucospilota and twofold dilution method was used to prepare serial concentration of the extracts (156 × 10 3 -4.75 g/mL) to make working solutions.",
